column36: HPV and Pap not due till 2018, everything was normal.
column66: Pt will return to see Dr. Perez in 1 year f/u 06/07/2018 9:00 AM. Pt received a script for PT for neck and a prosthesis Rx.
column96: complains hand/palm numbness, but prolly due to carpal tunnel from work. 1 year OV with Hagen, gave order for bra and prosthesis  6/5/19 at 9 am.
column126: Siona and UC do not accept Molina or any Medicaid HMO, called and faxed in appeal to Medicaid for auth to make purchase of bra and prosthesis.

column36: Discontinued Medicaid coverage, verified, and reinstated.     Scheduled DXMM 4/24 8:45 am and f/u w/Hagen 5/16 9am.    Waiting for Wong's appt from Alma.
column66: She couldn't see Danny Choy unless she choose a HMO Plan, so she wanted to see a PCP at Mercy.   Scheduled Dr. Olfa Najar at 2nd Fl DOC on 4/16 at 9:30 am.
column96: Scheduled and notified appt with Wong on 4/13 at 7:15 am.
column126: She missed appy with Wong because she thought the automated reminder phone call for her 4/16 PCP appt was to change Wong's appt from 4/13 to 4/16. Rescheduled her with Wong on 4/30 at 9:45 am.
column156: Called to DOC to make sure she got interpreter phone, then she came up to go over her discharge summary. Scheduled MRI, Ortho, and PCP f/u for her.
column186: Assisted with MRI and explained MM for tomorrow over the phone.
column243: lost cushioning in the knee, bone spur is growing, steroid injection today.
column273: Rescheduled and scheduled the following --   PCP Najar 5/16 8 am  Hagen 5/16 9 am  Miller 9/4 9 am  PT 6/13 11 am
column296: Confirmed over the phone with PCP on her medication changes --  Stop Ibuprofen, new Rx for Tylenol due on uncontrolled HTN. Added diuretic.

column36: She is first for surgery, will need to arrive by 5:30 am.
column66: Surgery Day. And Pt need to stay as inpatient for one night.
column96: drains were removed. only 1 LN were positive after removing 3. Will start radiation in about 4 wks.
column126: She didn't have a ride to go to f/u appt because husband was admitted to Mercy. So I called many different places to try to find a last min affordable rides for her. I was unable to find anything in short notice. Her husband got discharged in the end and were able to drive her.
column156: She was concerned that she was swelling up under arm and toward her back, but it turned out that is her brain and visually not used to that side without breast. Nothing was swollen everything is healing wonderfully.
column186: Explanation of side effects and risks, options to have treatment at Jackson Park Hospital with shorter wait because it would be 1 - 2hrs each day of waiting if she goes to Stroger. She will see the doctor every Monday to check on skin and progress during RT.
column214: DEXA scan. 2 possible anti-estrogen med: tamoxifen or arimidex. One has possible uterus Ca, the other has possible thinning of the bone density.
column243: Pt went through CAT Scan for the first radiation plan to make sure her position right. She has been put 3 marker spot. Schedule for the second appointment to mark the radiation area through X-Ray and will make appointments for her radiation therapy as well then.
column273: She will starts on Tamoxifen, and get pap annually. She was also prescibed Alendronate for oesteoprosis and Calcium. If she wants to get her tooth extract, she will need to call front desk Jackie to schedule the day before she wants the appt at 312.864.2292 after 9am.
column296: She saw Dr.McDunn and Dr. Monahan by herself. They gave her 1 month and 3 months follow up appt, but she will needs to reschedule the one in March because she plans to go back to China Jan to April. Dr. McDunn also supposedly referred her to a head scan but she didn't get any referral paperwork. They gave her next July MMG referral paper.

column36: There's a personnel transition, so I talked to the new in-charge person Michael Little about the pt's request. u
column66: Pt filled out NCCN's distress screening and is required to f/u with social worker. Call pt with Sarah to find out what is bothering her and what can we help. Transportation was one of her biggest concern, but she said the past few days is ok. She would like them to call 10 mins ahead not when they arrived so she has time to go downstairs. Other aren't big issues such as not having her children here, having cancer, and stomach problem after eating.
column96: Contacted Dept of Family and Support Services, they returned my call to inform me that someone went to see her on 1/13, received paperwork on 1/22, and she is approved to 125hrs/mo for 5hrs/day.
column126: Talked to In Home Care Inc about her increased hours. They did not received anything, so they will follow up with the regional agency directly. Explained pt's medical condition to her too.
column156: Calling back and forth many times with the home visit person. They wanted to scheduled next Wed 3/11, then called back later saying they were downstairs and wanted to go up right away. Call pt then call him back to tell him to go up, but pt called back later say no one went.
column186: Prescribed 3 month supplies of tamoxifen. She needs to continue with calcium and vit D supplement, 400 - 600 mg BID (twice a day). Could cause RA or gout, take Tylenol for pain or call if it's excessive. Stop osteoporosis med for now after 5 years of usage.     Patient didn't want to con't to see cardiology anymore, neither does she want colonoscopy as Dr.Zeng advised. She also refused to go to dermatology for her black spot on stomach.
column214: Ride was schedule, and she made it home for Dept of Aging home visit. She will finally have increased hours. Will see Dr. Perez next week to f/u after DXMM.
column243: 6 mo BL MMG, then f/u with Perez. Hardness on breast from surgery and RT, it will slowly soften down but won't be as soft as the other side. She is taking Tamoxifen and Vitamin D 1000 IU.
column273: Everything is normal, pt will come back in March 2016 for 6 mo R DXMM
column296: Everything is fine, still have some axillary numbness which is completely normal. Come back in 6 mo on 6/16/16 at 9 am.

column36: Called pt to let her know that I will be schedule f/u with Dr. Gasior for her. And asked her if she wants to go to Loyola to see a female med onc. She agreed and wanted me to schedule a gyne and dermo appt for her at Mercy too.
column66: Pt called back to let me know that she decided do not want to go up north for med onc anymore.
column96: 6 month f/u, she still refuse to see med onc or chemo, then disclosed she saw a 'beard mexican' doctor in a dirty clinic in 19th street. She showed us she has a bottle of anatrozole by a doctor name Marcia Salas, but this doc turned out to be PED and the clinic has no record of this pt. Shirley Wong supposed to be refilling it for her. She will come back for R DXMM for new lump and agreed to see Dr. Wong again.
column126: Pt is here for R side palp lump upper outer quadrant, but today she is saying there's a lump lengthwise under her nipple. Both area been US'ed and found nothing. Dr. Serena told her to f/u with Dr. Perez, I will message her on this. Pt continue to refuse to see Dr. Wong.
column156: Patient felt 2 lumps on her left side (she had a mastectomy). She also complained that she felt a lump on her right breast but had a DXMM at UIC in Aug 2016 on the right breast with no US. The result on her right breast DXMM at UIC (according to the patient) was normal. Dr. Weis advised to do US on both breast to see what the lumps are. Under the US, there are no masses just ribs that she felt.

column36: Surgery took less than 6 hours, stay in ICU for 1 night, NPO for 12 hours in case need to go back to surgery.
column66: Use vaseline or Aquaphor for scar to maintain hydration. Wait at least 3 to 4 months before dealing with nipple. No heavy lifting for 6 to 8 weeks. Don't strain the abdominal muscle. Removed one drain, will come back in 1.5 weeks for the 2nd.
column96: Visited pt at Prentice. She was doing well with min pain. She had some concern with cold spot on the skin and she was told that they used a small mesh in her abdomen muscle.
column126: see Perez in 6 mo on 5/3/18 at 9:45 am.

column36: NCCN Distress Screening and filled out CancerCare application.
column66: the last 2 of her CTA 7 days passes werent working. Calling CTA and ACS each twice to get her replacement cards. She wont get it for another 10 business days but there's not another way around.
column96: she start  taking the (Tamoxifen) once a day until to five year. She will come back for three month F/U on July 1, 2015. see Dr. Wong at 10am.
column126: She gave us all of her CTA passes but don't know which one worked or not. Called CTA to find out and mailed them back to ACS.
column156: everything is fine.7/1 10am Dr. Wong.7/23 9-11 Dr. Kanji.9-11 am
column186: she finish the Radiation at 4/3/15.  Dr. Wong said everything is okay, still taking the (Tamaxifen) come back for six month F/U DXMM. She need to come back six month F/U.
column214: she do the DXMM today everything is okay. She need to come back six month F/U. January, 2016
column243: everything is fine. 6 month R DXMM and see Perez in Jan 2016
column273: Shuping accompanied pt during DXMM.   Everything looks fine, nothing had changed. f/u in 6mnths (jan/ feb)
column296: 6mth f/u with Dr. Perez. Results from the MMG looks great. Everything looks fine. f/u with Dr. Perez in 6 mths with a MMG.

column36: Cindy accompanied pt with Dr. Wong f/u. Dr. Wong discussed bone scan results with pt. Pt returns for left scmm in July 2016 and f/u with Dr. Wong on 08/03/2016 8:30 AM.
column66: next MM on 7/19 at 9 am, Hagen on 11/16 at 8:30 am
column96: Accompanied pt to Dr. Wong f/u visit. Pt will return to see Dr Wong 12/07/2016 at 9:15 AM. Mammogram once a year is recommended for left side, July 2017.
column126: Return to OV in 6 month on 2/7 at 9:30 am. She will come back for OV every 6 months for 5 years after surgery, and MMG every 6 months for 2 years.
column156: Hagen wrote another whole body bone scan for her due to her left leg pain.   Next SCMM scheduled 7/21 8 am and see Hagen 8/29 8 am.
column186: pt did not want to get bone scan despite persistent bone pain on the left leg. explained to pt the previous scan was for a different location and before this new symptoms. she needs this bone scan as precautions.

column36: f/u with Dr. Wong everything was good, not much side effect from chemo. She chose a wig out of the one we had at the breast center.   She still did not hear anything from Dept of Aging, will f/u with them.
column66: Called Dept of Aging to follow up, they emailed to the regional office. Advise to call again in 3 weeks if nothing happened.
column96: Everything is good, come back in  a month before the next chemo.
column126: Scheduled to f/u with cardiovascular surgeon Dr. Gasior last month but it was rescheduled because he is on long term leave. His residents were supposed to f/u with her but Jewel says that they can't see pts without attending. Since they were here, the residents and Dr. Jones says okay, but then Jewel closed and blocked the schedule so she can't be seen in the end. Will find out if Dr. Perez want her to follow-up with anyone else.
column156: Dr. Wong. recommend her to see Dr. Kanji first, do the Radiation and do the born density too. And then  see Dr. Wong 08/25/15.
column186: she was the first time do the radiation 28 time. They will help her do the CT.
column214: she take off port today everything ok. come back for radiation.
column243: She thought she had RT already but it was just for measurement. She says her arm is very tight again. Dr. Perez gave her exercise to help that and advised to use lotion on her chest because it's very dry. Also gave her prescription for prothesis and bra, she will need a 6 mo f/u and see Dr. Gasior again.
column273: F/U with Dr. Bower he said the wound heal is very good. PT feel her should and the back of the neck is pain. Dr. Bower suggest she need to see PCP or Dr. Wong to F/u.
column296: Dr. Gasior checked on her DVT and he discussed with Dr. Wong that she doesn't need blood thinner anymore. Other joints pain are arthritis, Tylenol should help otherwise might need imaging after RT is done.

column36: Patient came in for her 3rd chemo treatment. her glucose is very high since 2/2/2016, they will inform dr. wong and also wants patient to see her pcp about it. Also had a wig fitter to head order her wig since the wig we gave does not fit her at all, it just fall off her head( too loose).
column66: Patient came for a fu after her 3th chemo. Patient denies any complains except tiredness from both legs. She received the wig from ACS but the color was too light. She wants to see if she can change to another one.
column96: Patient came in for the look good feel better event at Mercy hospital.
column126: Patient is still having a cold, she complains there's mucus in her throat and ask if she can take over the counter antibiotics that are sold in Chinatown. I talked to Alma about it and Alma asked Dr. Wong. Dr. Wong say do not self medicate she needs to see her pcp for medication.
column156: patient was in ER for her throat irritation. The ER dr. prescribed her antibiotics, cough syrup, nasal spray. Notified the infusion center about the medication and also notified Dr. Wong. Patient will resume chemo next week Friday(4/21/2017) instead of this Friday due to the medication she is on.
column186: Pt met with Dr. Wong. Will see him again on 06/23/2017. Continue chemo.
column243: everything okay she need come back for SCMM 09/22/17
column273: Cannot reschedule thyroid scan due to pre-auth was not approved

column36: Will ask Dr. Wong next week to look at 3 o'clock right at the nipple, small lump, just to be sure it's okay. Will schedule f/u appt with Pearl later.
column66: Next f/u with Dr. Wong on 3/9 10 am
column96: still waiting for Medicaid, will have to reschedule DXMM and other appt later.
column126: Everything is okay, just come back in June for BL MMG and see Wong again in 11/23 at 10 am
column186: everything is okay, f/u with Lt DXMM and OV in Dec 2016.
column214: Pt had DXMM before seeing Dr. Perez. DXMM was fine. Mammogram in six months. 06/15/2017 9:30 AM and Perez on 09/21/2017 1:00 AM.
column273: CXR, but took her 70 mins to get registered.
column296: Hagen rescheduled to 8/1 8:45 am, notified husband and Jenny Mei for ride.

column36: one week F/u she feel the wound still pain#4, and the toes , fingers feel numbness. DR Hagen take few stable out today and she need to come back one week again F/u.
column66: she stop the Chemo at 7x .Today see DR. Shirazi examination her wound, everything is oaky but her still fingers feel numbness. Doctor said that is normal. They don't has the schedule for her yet because she need to see DR. Wong on 11/05/15 8:30am let see what he say( should finish chemo or not. )After see DR. Wong let Pat know what is the next step than they can schedule her for Radiation.
column96: DR. Wong said can do the Radiation next, after the radiation she will see DR.Wong01/12/1610:30am.  He will give her the prescription for the pills. And he recommend she need to do the DEXA.
column126: staples removal.
